		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Andrew Boyd</span></strong> is an author, humorist, and twenty-year veteran of creative campaigns for social change. He&rsquo;s written two books of &ldquo;serious humor&rdquo; &mdash; <em>Daily Afflictions</em> and <em>Life&rsquo;s Little Deconstruction Book</em> (both W.W. Norton) &mdash; and is at work on two more: one about the irony of travel when there&rsquo;s no &ldquo;elsewhere&rdquo; anymore, and another about the &ldquo;odd challenges men face in a post-feminist world.&rdquo; He lives in New York City with his wee laptop.</p><a href="/contributors/andrew-boyd" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
